<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">34TH LVL AND UP, KEYS TO POWER</b></font> - <small>Gaeorn Kinslayer, BristleBain</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    At 34th, you need to buy ALL your spells you can! Also, you do need your research spells if you can get them. I got mine by doing a /w all necromancer and speaking to my brothers and sisters over 39th, to see if they had words of the spells allready to sell.<P> 

<P>

To REALLY cook, you need the following research spells<P>
<P>


Vampire Curse 29th<P>
Call of Bones 34th<P>

At 34th, we also get the BEST spell for soloing, ROOT! Now, to the startagy ....<P>

I will break this into 2 parts, soloing and grouping.<P>

A Soloing<P>

Where to hunt - <P>

Lower Guk- Near zone<P>
Sol B - Near zone<P>

Feerrott - Tree specter<P>


Lower Guk Dead side<P>

In LG, near zone, when you enter the zone, have GOT to keep Harmshield Mem'd, if you dont, you WILL DIE!
At the end of the entrence hall, 1 Froglok spans there, at the bottom of the ramp, 1 spawns on each side of the ramp. This is a good area to work.<P>


See a single frog, I lead off with root, an do it till it sticks. Back off, since they will continue to wack you. Next cast Boil Blood(BB), since this spell will not break the root, follow it up with Vampire curse, followed by Venom of Snake(VoS), then re-root, if it does break the root, just be calm and re root, the Vampire Curse will heal you. Next go with Call of Bones, the Vampire Curse(VC) will off set the drian of Call, thus VC will dump right into mana. Keep the root on, you need no othe casts on the frog, since just VoS and BB will kill a frog by themselves, with VC also, it is REALLY gonna die. IF you can keep Steelskin on, you can sometimes do 2 frogs at a time. WARNING! IF you are on the undead side(down ramp and to the right) and a frogs gets into the water and does not die in a second, RUN AND ZONE, or hit HARMSHIELD and run to zone and try to wait till the frog dies and then zone. Why you ask? Because just past the water there is the Bedroom, where 4 frog ghouls spawn, and if you prey gets near to them, they will ALL come, and even at 40th, 4 ghouls will kill you!<P>


Ferrott- Tree Specter<P>


In the Ferrott, there is the specter cave, which leads to fear. The cave has 6 specters. FORGET ABOUT SOLOING ANYTHING IN THE CAVE! Verant has made it so Specters will teleport on you if they can not hit you. What is the big deal you think? Specters have a HUGE AGRO area, thus trying to pull 1 will make its range hit anothers range, which will hit anothers range, and thus, if you are LUCKY, you will only have 3 specters on you, and once agian, even at 40th, this is pretty much suicidial. BUT, near the cave is a tree on a hill where a single specter spawns, thus good hunting.<P>


Spells you need<P>


Panic Dead<P>

VC<P>

VoS<P>

Some form of Darkness spell<P>

Call of Bones<P>

BB<P>

Some Drain<P>


I like to use my pet also, but that is up to you. Lead off with your darkness, followed by Panic. As soon as you have the specter turned, Lay on your DotS,VoS,BB,VC, then hit your Call of Bones. Re-apply your Panic, and count, BB lasts 30 seconds,VoS, 60 seconds. Just keep it running, and normally 1 series of DoTs and 1 extra BB, and you have 1 dead specter. You also might want to use use form of Undead DD spell, since we dont often use evocation, and Ignite Bones, our 44th lvl Direct Damage spell, uses this skill. Thus specters and froglok ghouls are GREAT for us to raise this skill.<P>


B Grouping<P>


When you are in a group, at 34th and on, you have 2 ways to go, with pet, or with out.<P>


With Pet- Spell to have mem'd<P>

VoS<P>

VC<P>

BB<P>

Intensify Death<P>

Renew Bones<P>

 If you are going to use your pet in a group, HOT KEY, HOT KEY, HOT KEY your pet commands! A out of control pet will make you VERY un-wanted.
If I am going to use a pet, I find out where we are going to camp, or if we are going to clear our way around. It is best to have a base area to pull to. IF this is the case, wait to make your pet there, and have it guard next to you. This will keep your pet in the area. Also, find who is going to be the main tank. The reason is that you can make your pet help drop your groups main target FAST. Nothing makes you tanks happier than your pet windmilling on the main taget of the group. Remember at all times, keep your pet in sight, do NOT let it chase, that is why you have tanks. A pet chasing a MOB is allmost the #1 reason for pet made trains. Also, keep your pet buffed and healed.<P>

  You as the caster sould toss in at most 2 DoTs into a Battle, to keep your mana up, and the pet is going to do alot of damage anyway, so it is a good idea to keep your mana high. I like to toss BB and VC, while staying in Bone form, from Callo of Bones, since a staedy stream of fighting will allow VC to keep the mana flowing back in, thus you will be a mana battery.
<P>

No Pet.<P>


Without a pet, you sould find out who is on root duty. If you need to be on it, easy, if you are fighting undead, you will really rock, since Hungry Earth is a root spell that does around 48pts of damage AND root. My spell choices for hunting without a pet are<P>

VoS<P>

BB<P>

VC<P>

CoB(Call of Bones)<P>

Root<P>

Harmshield<P>


You action s pretty much like solo, excpet you assist off your main tank, and help drop things FAST!
If you group is smart, you will have a rather steady flow of blue con MobS, thus you can keep Call of Bones up, and with VC, keep the mana flowing.<P>


One last word, if you are unsure about a group, or where you are going, keep Gate mem'd till the group can show you they know what they are doing. At 34th and up, in Sol B and LG, you can get into some areas that is you are not smart, after you die, without some 40lvl and up help, you can allmost forget your corpse and all you items. Some areas in LG, there are SO many MOBs, that getting your body is allmost impossable with out MAJOR help.<P>


Well, that is about it. At 39th, the only change is you have Scourge, which, unless you are in a LONG fight, is too slow to be worth casting. The one spell that is worth changing anything for is Augment Dead. This pet buff spell you can BUY! YES, buy it. It makes a MAJOR diffrence in your pet! It will get 1, if not 2 more attacks, and add 8 to 10pts of damage per hit your pet gets! Thus, if you are going to use a pet, this spell is a MUST have!<P>


Good hunting!
 
    </small></font></p>
